            and they are much more widespread than commonly assumed. One out of
            ten women, so the current hypothesis, struggles with Anorexia,
            Bulimia, Binge Eating or another form of the phenomenon. Research
            confirms that especially those living in industrialized countries
            are at highest risk to be affected.
        </p>
